TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {29877=2013 - Photos 2013 Statistics , 30369=Before UNH (Signing Day Video) An explosive, versatile athlete out of East Bridgewater High School in southeastern Mass. ... senior team captain was twice named Boston Globe All-Scholastic and Boston Herald All-Scholastic ... feted as the 2011 Division 4 Player of the Year ... three-time Brockton Enterprise All-Scholastic ... garnered 2010 Defensive Player of the Year honors ... named 2011 Offensive Player of the Year ... garnered ESPN Boston All-State Team honors as a defensive back ... earned the WATD South Shore League Player of the Year award twice ... three-time South Shore League All-Star ... amassed 62 TDs on 2,912 yards rushing, 1,135 yards receiving and, on defense, intercepted 11 passes in career ... school record-holder in winter track 55-meter dash ... tabbed to the Division 4 State Relay Championship Team ... two-year captain on the baseball team ... selected as a South Shore League All-Star in 2010 and 2011 ... vice president of the East Bridgewater National Honor Society and a member of the school's executive committee, 29537=UNH HIGHLIGHTS 2013 Appeared in 14 regular season games... Had a total of 69 tackles (49 solo) on the season ranking 4th on the team...Also had 3 interceptions which ranked 2nd on the team... His 20 pass break-ups led the team, 30227=2012 Redshirt season ... named to CAA Academic All-Conference Team, 28988=Personal The son of John and Mariellen DeAndrade ... born 2-15-94 in Brockton, Mass. ... brother, Justin, played football at Worcester State ... sister, Nicole, inducted into Salve Regina Hall of Fame for basketball}
